modules.description: Processes hierarchical path patterns to route requests to corresponding handlers, supporting dynamic segments and wildcards. Operates on strings representing paths and functions that handle matched routes. Used to implement URL routing in web servers and navigate nested data structures in client applications.

Handles path-based routing for web applications by matching URL fragments to predefined handlers. Processes routes defined as `Dispatch.t` and triggers corresponding actions based on the current fragment. Initializes the fragment to a specified value or "/" if none is given, and executes a fallback handler when no route matches.
